cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and their vulnerability to adversarial examples, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The focus on manifold-based defenses also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG), but this is less likely given the emphasis on machine learning and generative models.
